<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> "Benjamin Franklin...urged Voltaire to become a freemason; and Voltaire agreed, perhaps only to please Franklin.<cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFRidley.2C_Jasper2002">Ridley, Jasper (2002). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=ISMObxdcmfsC&amp;pg=RA4-PA112&amp;dq=freemason+voltaire&amp;ei=ssVASJfIOKakiwGz44zbCQ&amp;sig=DSRHtjUrh3wTLPDfM9SiyFTyvyg" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=ISMObxdcmfsC&amp;pg=RA4-PA112&amp;dq=freemason+voltaire&amp;ei=ssVASJfIOKakiwGz44zbCQ&amp;sig=DSRHtjUrh3wTLPDfM9SiyFTyvyg" rel="nofollow">The Freemasons: A History of the World's Most Powerful Secret Society</a></i>. pp.&#160;p.112<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=ISMObxdcmfsC&amp;pg=RA4-PA112&amp;dq=freemason+voltaire&amp;ei=ssVASJfIOKakiwGz44zbCQ&amp;sig=DSRHtjUrh3wTLPDfM9SiyFTyvyg" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=ISMObxdcmfsC&amp;pg=RA4-PA112&amp;dq=freemason+voltaire&amp;ei=ssVASJfIOKakiwGz44zbCQ&amp;sig=DSRHtjUrh3wTLPDfM9SiyFTyvyg" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=ISMObxdcmfsC&amp;pg=RA4-PA112&amp;dq=freemason+voltaire&amp;ei=ssVASJfIOKakiwGz44zbCQ&amp;sig=DSRHtjUrh3wTLPDfM9SiyFTyvyg</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Freemasons%3A+A+History+of+the+World%27s+Most+Powerful+Secret+Society&amp;rft.aulast=Ridley%2C+Jasper&amp;rft.au=Ridley%2C+Jasper&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3Bp.112&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DISMObxdcmfsC%26pg%3DRA4-PA112%26dq%3Dfreemason%2Bvoltaire%26ei%3DssVASJfIOKakiwGz44zbCQ%26sig%3DDSRHtjUrh3wTLPDfM9SiyFTyvyg&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Voltaire"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> See also: <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.americanmason.com/didntARC